      "@id": "#biosample-1",
      "@type": "BioSample",
      "name": "HuC:loxp-DsRed-loxp-GFP, HSP-Cre ~ neuron",
      "description": "The medaka brain deriverd from two transgenic lines. One is the transgenic line (Tg (HuC:loxp-DsRed-loxp-GFP)) that visualized neural progenitors by the HuC promoter. The second is a line (Tg (HSP-Cre)) that expresses Cre recombinase under the heat shock protein promoter. In the absence of the recombination, DsRed is expressed in the neural progenitor cells. When Cre-loxp recombination is induced the neural progenitors express GFP instead of DsRed.",
